{"doc":{"isMarkdown":false,"isTranslated":true,"isActive":true,"flaws":{},"title":"has-same-node","mdn_url":"/es/docs/Web/EXSLT/set/has-same-node","locale":"es","native":"Español","sidebarHTML":"","body":[{"type":"prose","value":{"id":null,"title":null,"isH3":false,"content":"<p></p><div style=\"background:#f5f5f5; margin: 5px 0;\" id=\"sect1\">\n    <b><a href=\"/es/docs/Web/XSLT/Transforming_XML_with_XSLT#referencia_de_xslt.2fxpath\">Referencia de XSLT y XPath</a></b>: <a href=\"/es/docs/Web/XSLT/Element\">Elementos XSLT</a>, <a href=\"/es/docs/Web/EXSLT\">Funciones EXSLT</a>, <ahref=\" es=\"\" docs=\"\" web=\"\" xpath=\"\" funciones\"=\"\">XPath:Funciones, <a href=\"/es/docs/Web/XPath/Axes\">XPath:Ejes</a>\n</ahref=\"></div><p></p>\n\n<p><br>\n <code>set:has-same-node()</code> determina si dos conjuntos de nodos tienen algún nodo en común.</p>"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"sintaxis","title":"Sintaxis","isH3":true,"content":"<pre class=\"eval notranslate\">set:has-same-node(<em>conjuntoNodos1</em>,<em>conjuntoNodos2</em>)\n</pre>"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"argumentos","title":"Argumentos","isH3":true,"content":"<dl>\n <dt id=\"conjuntonodos1\"><code><em>conjuntoNodos1</em></code></dt>\n <dd>El primer conjunto de nodos a revisar.</dd>\n <dt id=\"conjuntonodos2\"><code><em>conjuntoNodos2</em></code></dt>\n <dd>El segundo conjunto de nodos a revisar.</dd>\n</dl>"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"devuelve","title":"Devuelve","isH3":true,"content":"<p><code>true</code> si los dos conjuntos de nodos tienen algún nodo en común; de otro modo <code>false</code>.</p>"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"definido_en","title":"Definido en","isH3":true,"content":"<p><a class=\"external\" href=\"http://www.exslt.org/set/functions/has-same-node/index.html\" rel=\" noopener\">EXSLT - SET:HAS-SAME-NODE</a></p>"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"implementaci.c3.b3n_de_gecko","title":"Implementación de Gecko","isH3":true,"content":"<p>Implementado en Gecko 1.9 y posteriores.</p>"}}],"toc":[],"summary":"set:has-same-node() determina si dos conjuntos de nodos tienen algún nodo en común.","popularity":0,"modified":"2022-07-19T02:29:32.000Z","other_translations":[{"title":"set:has-same-node()","locale":"en-US","native":"English (US)"},{"title":"has-same-node","locale":"fr","native":"Français"}],"source":{"folder":"es/web/exslt/set/has-same-node","github_url":"https://github.com/mdn/translated-content/blob/main/files/es/web/exslt/set/has-same-node/index.html","last_commit_url":"https://github.com/mdn/translated-content/commit/5fe4ab11259b37914fab41914e84897fea47d143","filename":"index.html"},"parents":[{"uri":"/es/docs/Web","title":"Tecnología para desarrolladores web"},{"uri":"/es/docs/Web/EXSLT","title":"EXSLT"},{"uri":"/es/docs/Web/EXSLT/set","title":"Sets (set)"},{"uri":"/es/docs/Web/EXSLT/set/has-same-node","title":"has-same-node"}],"pageTitle":"has-same-node - EXSLT | MDN","noIndexing":false}}